COVID19 Update(Nigeria): 
confirmed 0, deaths 0, recovered 0 Coronavirus spread in Nigeria is beginning to defy the lockdown in key cities as government officials worry over the gross capacity gap in testing the population. Since the first case of the virus was reported on February 27, Nigeria has now recorded a total of 493 cases, 362 of that number coming after the lockdown was first imposed on March 30. From Feb 27 when the first case was recorded in Nigeria, it took 28 days for the total number of cases to reach 51. In one day alone yesterday, Nigeria registered 51 new cases of Coronavirus Source: Business Day Check your inbox or spam folder to confirm your subscription. COVID19 Update(Nigeria): As much as half of the 18 sub-Saharan Africa countries surveyed by the International Monetary Fund (IMF) will see their economies contract in 2020, with two of the continent’s economic heavyweights leading the decline. South Africa, with the largest economy after Nigeria, is forecast to record the biggest… April 15, 2020 In "News" COVID19 Update(Nigeria): Illustrative, Medical staff By Chioma Obinna Despite the lockdown imposed by President Muhammadu Buhari on Lagos State, the epicentre of coronavirus, neighbouring Ogun and Abuja, the Federal Capital Territory (FCT), to stem the spread of the virus, figures show that COVID-19 confirmed cases have more than double across… April 12, 2020 In "News" COVID19 Update(Nigeria): By David Royal 362 COVD-19 cases have been recorded in Nigeria since the outbreak of the pandemic in the country, Vanguard can report. The Federal Ministry of Health confirmed the first coronavirus disease (COVID-19) case in Lagos State, Nigeria. The case, which was confirmed on the 27th of… April 14, 2020 In "News"